# Ticket conventions

## Prerequisite

Tickets are derived from a technical plan in `thoughts/plans/`. Never create tickets without a plan.

## File naming

- Index: `README.md` — table mapping order → file → focus
- Tickets: `NN-kebab-summary.md` (zero-padded number, e.g. `01-shell-navigation.md`)

## README.md structure

```markdown
# Implementation tickets (topic)

Ordered work items derived from [`../plans/MM-DD-YYYY-topic-technical-plan.md`](../plans/...).

| Order | Ticket | Focus |
|------:|--------|-------|
| 1 | [`01-slug.md`](01-slug.md) | Brief focus description |
```

## Ticket structure

```markdown
# Ticket NN — Short title

**Status:** Draft | In Progress | Done
**Depends on:** ticket number or "—"
**Plan:** [link](../plans/...)
**PRD:** [link](../prds/...) §sections
**Design:** [link](../designs/...)

## Summary
## Scope
## Out of scope (later tickets)
## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Checkboxes for each criterion
## Estimate
**S** | **M** | **L**
```

**Key rules:**
- Every ticket links back to its plan, PRD, and design with relative paths
- Reference specific PRD sections with § notation
- Acceptance criteria use `- [ ]` checkboxes
- Keep scope tight — one demoable unit of work per ticket
- Note dependencies between tickets explicitly
